just_use referee_conformance_test.go

# label: GENERATED
# role: emitted Go referee tests — do NOT hand-edit

One Test_ function per scenario in `games/lynrummy/conformance/scenarios/referee.dsl`.
Each test drives `ValidateGameMove` or `ValidateTurnComplete`
and asserts the referee's `RefereeStage` + message substring
against the DSL expectation.

Regenerate after any DSL edit:

    go run ./cmd/fixturegen ./games/lynrummy/conformance/scenarios/*.dsl

Enumerate-and-bridge peer: the same DSL scenarios drive
`games/lynrummy/elm-port-docs/tests/LynRummy/DslConformanceTest.elm`.
Go and Elm referees must agree on every scenario; divergent
pass/fail counts mean one side drifted.

